parameters:
I'm Masamune Kashin, who transferred here today
and will be staying in the dormitory.

Oh, now that I think about it... the teacher
said... today is the day for moving into the
dormitory.

I'm Tommy D. One. I'm going to be a roommate, so
just call me Tommy.

Ah, Tommy. Nice to meet you. I'm Masamune, it's
good to be roommates.
Yeah, nice to meet you, Masamune-kun.

(It's definitely a guy... with a gender-neutral
appearance, and I felt a little flutter)
(If we don't get used to living together soon)

Actually, the housemaster was supposed to give us
a dormitory explanation, but they're currently
absent due to illness.
That's why I was asked to explain instead.

Ah, the housemaster refers to the experienced
teacher who supports our life in the dormitory.

I see. Since you're from the Empire, it's helpful
that you can tell me more in detail.

You came from quite a distant place, huh, the
Empire.

But there are also classmates from the Empire, so
it's okay.

If you have anything you want to ask, feel free to
ask.
Afterwards, I'll give you a tour of the dormitory.

Caledony Magic Academy is a boarding school.
Except for long breaks, we basically spend our
time in the dormitory.

There are three dormitories, Howard Dormitory,
Bailey Dormitory, and Clark Dormitory.

The names were taken from the first housemasters,
so there aren't any particular differences between
the dormitories.

The dormitory is located on the 6th floor, which
is the top floor of the school building. That's
why going to school is really easy.

So, let's get along since we'll be spending time
in the same room until graduation!
カレドニー魔法学院について
I'm not very familiar with the Empire.

I grew up in the Kingdom of Greatland, so ever
since I realized I had talent for magic, I've
always wanted to enter.

At the oldest magic academy, students from all
over the world gather.

Of course, there is a strict entrance exam for
admission, and you can't get in without magical
talent.

Besides, the tuition fees are high, and it might
be impossible unless you come from an upper-
middle-class... um, a family of higher social
status in the middle class.

Although it's a small number, there is a
scholarship system though.

In return, you can take high-level classes. There
are also many famous wizards among the graduates.

It will also be advantageous for employment in the
Magic Association!

But the school is located in the northern part of
the kingdom, at the forefront of battle against
demons.
Actually, demons often appear around there...

Caledony Magic Academy is divided into middle
school and high school sections.

We're second-year students in the high school
section. Just like a regular school, we also have
classes like math.

But since magic classes are the main focus, there
aren't as many of them.

Magic classes are optional. You can choose from
classes like Basic Magic, Curse Magic, and Ritual
Studies.

Since magic is different for each person, studying
magic that you're not good at would just be a
waste of time.

Just like a regular school, we also have clubs. Of
course, not everyone is in one though.

We also have regular clubs like the soccer club,
but since we can't participate in tournaments,
they're not popular.

The most popular one is the Magic Research Club.
But it's not like anyone can join there...

Don't worry, there are plenty of magic-related
clubs and study groups.
Then, let me show you around Howard Dormitory.
